Some Gautrain routes won't be operational this weekend due to maintenance. Gautrain has advised commuters that there will be no train services between Centurion, Pretoria and Hatfield over the weekend. Spokesperson Kesagee Nayager said Gautrain has put measures in place to assist affected commuters. “During this time – a bus service will operate at 30 minute intervals, and will transport passengers between the affected stations free of charge. The parking facilities at Pretoria and Hatfield stations will be available, and the airport service and trains between Park and Centurion stations will not be affected and will operate according to schedule.” Said Kesagee Nayager.